rn ideas and social pursuits which in turn affected different facets of society and culture in Japan, Korea and Taiwan. The study illustrates how the British missionaries’ intent to introduce Christianity was affected by the response of the East Asians to Western ideas. In describing the high drama of the British missionary movement’s pioneering days in the late nineteenth century to its persecution during the late 1930s, Ion casts light on a particular, yet important, aspect of the changing tides of Anglo-Japanese relations. This book will ably complement his previous study of Canadian missionaries in East Asia during the same period. Chosen as one of the 15 outstanding books of 1993 for mission studies by the International Bulletin of Missionary Research  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aMissions canadiennesxHistoirexCorée. 0aMissions canadiennesxHistoirexJapon. 0aMissions canadiennesxHistoirexTaiwan. 0aMissionsxEast Asia. 0aMissionsxJapan. 0aMissionszEast Asia. 0aMissionszJapan. 0aMissions, BritishxHistoryxEast Asia. 0aMissions, BritishxHistoryxJapan. 0aMissions, BritishzEast AsiaxHistory. 0aMissions, BritishzJapanxHistory. 0aMissions, British. 0aMissions, CanadianxHistoryxEast Asia. 0aMissions, CanadianxHistoryxJapan. 0aMissions, CanadianzEast AsiaxHistory. 0aMissions, CanadianzJapanxHistory. 0aProtestant churchesxMissionsxHistoryxEast Asia. 0aProtestant churchesxMissionsxHistoryxJapan. 0aProtestant churchesxMissionszEast AsiaxHistory. 0aProtestant churchesxMissionszJapanxHistory. 0aProtestant churchesxMissionszKoreaxHistory. 0aProtestant churchesxMissionszTaiwanxHistory. 0aÉglises protestantesxMissionsxHistoirexCorée. 0aÉglises protestantesxMissionsxHistoirexJapon. 0aÉglises protestantesxMissionsxHistoirexTaiwan. 4a